Manchester City coach, Pep Guardiola has named his side’s squad to tackle Chelsea in the Champions League final tie on Saturday night in Portugal. Guardiola released a 24-man squad to face Chelsea at the Estádio do Dragão in a post via Man City’s website. Man City had knocked Paris Saint-Germain out of the Champions League semi-final stage earlier this month, while Chelsea eliminated Real Madrid. The Premier League champions head to the game following a 5-0 victory over Everton in their last fixture, while Chelsea was defeated 2-1 by Aston Villa. Below is Man City’s squad against Chelsea: Kyle Walker, Rúben Dias, John Stones, Nathan Aké, Raheem Sterling, Ilkay Gündogan , Gabriel Jesus, Sergio Agüero, Oleksandr Zinchenko, Zack Steffen, Aymeric Laporte, Rodrigo, Kevin De Bruyne, Bernardo Silva, Ferran Torres, Benjamin Mendy, Fernandinho, Riyad Mahrez, João Cancelo, Ederson, Scott Carson, Phil Foden, Eric Garcia, James Trafford. The kick-off time for Man City vs Chelsea is 8 pm, Nigerian time. Champions League: You won’t beat me again – Guardiola warns Tuchel 